function setCookie( name, value, expires, path, domain, secure ) {
var today = new Date();
today.setTime( today.getTime() );
if ( expires ) {
expires = expires * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24;
}
var expires_date = new Date( today.getTime() + (expires) );
document.cookie = name+'='+escape( value ) +
( ( expires ) ? ';expires='+expires_date.toGMTString() : '' ) +
( ( path ) ? ';path=' + path : '' ) +
( ( domain ) ? ';domain=' + domain : '' ) +
( ( secure ) ? ';secure' : '' );
}
//----------------------------------------------------------
// check if cookie defined
//----------------------------------------------------------
function getCookie(name) {
var start = document.cookie.indexOf( name + "=" );
var len = start + name.length + 1;
if ( ( !start ) && ( name != document.cookie.substring( 0, name.length ) ) ) {
return null;
}
if ( start == -1 ) return null;
var end = document.cookie.indexOf( ';', len );
if ( end == -1 ) end = document.cookie.length;
return unescape( document.cookie.substring( len, end ) );
}
//------------------------------------------------------------
// Remove cookie
//------------------------------------------------------------
function removeCookie( name, path, domain) {
if ( getCookie( name ) )
{
document.cookie = name + '=' + ( ( path ) ? ';path=' + path : '') + ( ( domain ) ? ';domain=' + domain : '' ) + ';expires=Thu, 01-Jan-1970 00:00:01 GMT';
}
}

}
return domainname;
}

<div class="commentary-section">
<p>
<b>1.27pm</b> The two local umpires - S Ravi and C Shamshuddin - walk out, a rare sight in international cricket, as the crowd cheers. Rohit Sharma and Shikhar Dhawan stroll out too, in the sapping heat. Alagappan says the crowd is only about 60% right now. Odd, since the festive season has begun in India. Dale Steyn has the new ball, he'll bowl to Rohit with two slips...
</p>
<p>
Narendra: "Interestingly all 3 Subcontinent teams batting firs today."
</p>
<p>
<b>India</b> have won the toss, they are <b>batting</b> first, with the <strong>same XI</strong>.
</p>
<p>
<strong>MS Dhoni</strong>: The pitch is likely to slow down later, lots depends on dew though it comes in very late. Batting first is something we are good at, though we chase well too. We don't want to repeat the mistakes we have done, we have played good cricket, but we have not finished games.
</p>
<p>
<strong>AB de Villeirs</strong>: We would have batted first too, it's a big toss to lose for us. It will be disappointing if we don't win here. We have two changes as Morkel and Duminy are injured, so Aaron Phangiso and Chris Morris come in. Two frontline bowlers coming in for us in the team. Don't think a lot of people expected us leading after the three matches.
</p>
<p>
We'll have to wait and watch if SA continue to open with Miller or not, but they have two frontline spinners and three pacers including Morris.
</p>
<p>
<b>12.45pm</b> Our man Alagappan at the ground: "Am here, but the crowd isn't, plus there are those three empty stands. <strong>Morne Morkel</strong> is going through his warm-ups with Steyn and the rest. S Aravind has also had a go, the left-arm variation working for him?" Ten minutes for the toss, SA will have to make a forced change for Duminy, let's see if Morkel is fit to play or not and what India have in store. The <strong>pitch</strong> looks rather dry and there are some prominent cracks too, likely to assist spinners according to Gavaskar and Anil Kumble. Most of the experts say batting first is a good option.
</p>
<p>
Shishank Dahiya: "Dont forget that Raina is coming at the end of innings and has been asked to score quickly, which is not easy. Even he would want to come 1 down and take his time and score a century."
</p>
<p>
Mindreader: "Raina should do a Bevan not Duminy...Bevan was the best in finding gaps and look for 2's and odd boundaries..within no time you see his score will be in 20s/30s"
</p>
<p>
<b>12.35pm</b> The sun is out and the humidity is about 55% to heat things up in Chennai. South Africa do not have fond memories of their <a href="http://www.espncricinfo.com/icc_cricket_worldcup2011/engine/match/433579.html" target="_blank">last match</a> here while many Indian fans would say this is almost a home ground for captain MS Dhoni. Hello and welcome to our coverage of the fourth ODI, with the series 2-1 in SA's favour, I'm Vishal Dikshit and will be your entertainer for the day.
</p>
<p>
A few issues for both teams to tackle here - India's batting line-up isn't settled, they haven't scored properly in the death over, SA have lost JP Duminy for the rest of the series due to injury, Hashim Amla and David Miller haven't scored much. Actually, you should read Firdose's <a href="http://www.espncricinfo.com/india-v-south-africa-2015-16/content/story/931174.html" target="_blank">preview here</a> for everything.
</p>
<p>
Boopathi P: "I am expecting rayadu instead of Raina..." Two ducks in a row aren't great but unlikely that India will leave out Suresh Raina. Sunil Gavaskar has said his form is not an issue, it's his shot selection.
</p>
<p>
Nirmal: "Hi All really excited to see today, just remember Gurkeerat performance in the last month hope he will get a chance today."
</p>
<p>
"Tough day at office today, WI vs SRI, SA VS IND and PAK vs ENG ..and top of that end of week (Kuwait)" Extended weekend, Yasir? There's a Zimbabwe v Afghanistan ODI too, where Zimbabwe are batting first.
</p>

<p class="commsText">
<b>5.26pm</b> Will South Africa be unhappy with this total? India looked set to score 320 at one point when Kohli was batting with Rahane and later with Raina and conditions looked good for batting. India batted well in the middle overs and the running between the wicket was impressive too, mainly because of Kohli. What a fluent hundred from him today, clean boundaries, finding the gaps easily and never looking in trouble. He kept on batting till the end and eventually got out because of cramps, his first hundred since the World Cup. South Africa, on the other hand, kept using their short ball weapon and used it effectively in the death overs too, to keep India to 299 for 8. The hosts scored 69 for 5 in the last 10, and do join us for the chase soon...
